# TypeScript Standards

## Error Handling

```typescript
// ❌ BAD – silent catch
try { await fetchData(); } catch (e) {}

// ✅ GOOD – log and rethrow or handle
try {
  await fetchData();
} catch (e) {
  console.error('Failed to fetch', { error: e });
  throw new Error('Unable to retrieve data', { cause: e });
}
```

## Types
- Prefer explicit return types on exported functions
- Use `interface` for object shapes; avoid `any` unless for third-party interop
- Leverage shared types in `types/` (e.g. `accounting.ts`, `pos.ts`, `sync.ts`)
